# Git attributes for evolve-loop.
#
# export-ignore is honored by `git archive` (when producing tarballs from
# git). It tells `git archive` to exclude matching paths from the generated
# archive. This is the standard mechanism for "track in repo, exclude from
# distribution tarballs".
#
# Note: Claude Code's plugin installer does NOT currently use `git archive` —
# it clones the source repo and applies a separate hardcoded filter — so
# the `knowledge-base/` directive here may be a no-op for /plugin install.
# We declare it anyway because:
#   1. It's the standard Git mechanism (documentation-as-config)
#   2. Other consumers (Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, manual `git archive` users)
#      may honor it
#   3. Future Claude Code versions may honor it
#
# See docs/architecture/knowledge-base.md for the full architecture.

knowledge-base/ export-ignore
